  "time_ut": 1660795503,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0dcf\u0db8\u0dbd\u0dca\u0da7 \u0d87\u0db8\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dc0\u0da7 Black Cap Movement \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dca\u0db0 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Black Cap Movement opposes giving Namal a ministry",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Black Cap Movement organization says that there is currently a rumor spreading in the political community that Parliament member Namal Rajapaksa has requested to be given a strong minister in the all-party or national government to be formed in the future and their organization is paying close attention to this.",
        "The Black Cap Movement, which was one of the organizations that participated in the Gallumuwadora struggle, says that the main goal of the people's struggle in the country against the tyranny of Rajapakse familyism was to create a new regime without Rajapakseism.",
        "\"The people did not expect the old Pohottu government to come back to the fore through the struggle. A country without the backwardness of Rajapaksaism. But we noticed that Namal Rajapaksa has recently pressured the Minister of Environment through two letters to appoint a high-ranking official of the Bureau of Geological Survey and Mines.",
        "Also, political sources mention that there are preparations to appoint Namal Rajapaksa MP as the National Organizer of Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna. If the Rajapaksa cartel continues to trigger the people without any sensitivity to the people's opinion, the people will decide their political fate in the next election.",
        "But before that, we very seriously request all political groups not to allow the all-party government that is being formed to find solutions to the crisis in Sri Lanka to become Namalla's political gamble.",
        "The innocent people of the country are ultimately affected by the political games of the Namal Rajapaksa and we believe that it is the responsibility of all political activists to build the land that all the peaceful fighters who engaged in non-violent struggle hoped for.\" The organization further says in its announcement."
      ],
